# Week2 Cursor Rules

Scope: Applies to this folder (`Week2/`) and all files inside it.

## General
- Keep changes beginner-friendly and easy to read.
- Prefer small, focused edits over large rewrites.
- Preserve existing filenames and folder structure unless explicitly asked.

## Python (`*.py`)
- Follow PEP 8 basics (clear names, consistent spacing, short functions).
- Add brief docstrings for functions.
- Use comments only when logic is not obvious.
- Prefer simple built-in tools and standard library modules.
- Do not add new dependencies unless explicitly requested.

## CSV/Data Files (`*.csv`)
- Do not modify source data values unless explicitly requested.
- Keep column headers unchanged.
- Preserve row order unless task requires sorting/filtering.

## Markdown (`*.md`)
- Keep writing concise and student-friendly.
- Use clear section headers and short bullet lists.
- Avoid unnecessary formatting complexity.

## Safety
- Never delete project files without explicit confirmation.
- If a request could overwrite important work, ask before proceeding.
